      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in museum-quality condition. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies to deliver a linear power band and a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory Variable M Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution. This vehicle has been meticulously maintained with documented subframe reinforcement, a comprehensive VANOS overhaul, and recent rod bearing prophylaxis. The chassis retains its original rigidity, complemented by a perfectly calibrated suspension and OEM cross-drilled rotors. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic with an immaculate interior and zero undercarriage oxidation, this M3 represents the pinnacle of mechanical purity for the discerning collector.",
